           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Probably its not something new but I'd like to share my observations about flee health of mobs and you guys might find it usefull in a some way...<br />a) Mobs in PoS/PoV will flee once their health drop below your <i> max </i> health<br />What this mean? Runes dont counts - only your natural hp and your HP buffs. How it work? <br />My hp raid buffed 4700+ - golems flee @18% health<br />My hp after aego+maelin ~3500 - golems flee @13%<br />My hp self buffed with maelin ~2400 - golems flee @8%<br />All this VERY consistent and reporduciable accodring to infomation above my guess would be that golems have ~25000-26000hp<br />Moral: if you want have extra time for meditation while agro kite - get yourself as many hp buffs as you can<br />b) Selfheal moment for mobs in PoS/PoV depend only on flee health<br />Mob will heal self on +10% ONLY in 1 case if in the moment then health of mob drop below "flee" lvl you are out of casting range<br />I hope this information could be usefull and wonder if ppl observed same in other places..</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
