                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I have observed nothing of the like.<br /><br />For starters, mobs tend to flee at different % depending on how much health I have at the time.  If I am at full health, they could easily flee at 18%.  If I am under 90%, they usually don't turn until 8%.<br /><br />When they self heal, they heal ~ 20%, not 10%.  They self heal if you are outside of melee range, not casting range.  In fact, I have had so many self heal on me, I long ago began to insist moving to sit almost on top of the mob the second I notice he has turned to flee.  I have also generally begun casting Saryrn's Kiss at around 25-30% health to expedite the flee decision.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
