                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Original poster is correct.  This has been the case since I started aggro kiting in PoP.  You can observed the effects directly by doing exactly what he said, try it out with raid buffs, self-buffs, etc...  <br /><br />This is the behavior I observed when aggro kiting frogs and golems.  If you wish to test the theory, fight a golem with 4k+ max hp, but let your hp slip at the end of the fight, maybe drop below half.  Notice that golem/frog doesn't flee for quite some time, maybe even getting an enrage off.  Now, repeat, but be around full health when the mob drops down below 20%, note that he's fleeing early now.  <br /><br />The %'s I can't verify, because I don't recall, but the AI is definately coded like that.  That's the one reason I would ask for a virtue when I was soloing in valor.  MUCH more convenient when the mob flees before enrage, don't have to think about pet.  Now I guess it's less of an issue, but I used to hate to lose Jabober to freak accidents.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
