                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The "PoP regen" thing I think has something to do with you being out of the mob's agro range.    I don't think it's the casting range or the melee range but the agro range.  It probably also has something to do with the fact that higher level mobs regen a lot quicker when they are "not agroed".  It's gotta be a bug in the way the "retreat" mode works.  Those PoV golems have always done that when I hunted there soon after PoP's release (probably somewhere between a week or two weeks since I didn't buy the expansion until the week after launch).  When they got low I would always have to kite closer to them, not nearly melee range but close enough for agro range or else they would do the magical regeneration thing or would warp to their spawn point.  I left there for Halls of Honor about 3 weeks into PoP's launch though (when I turned level 65) and since stuff there didn't flee I never had a problem with the PoP mob regen thing.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
