                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I think there might also be a level component in this "flee-mode" AI code.<br /><br />I've seen mobs self-heal in flee mode when I've been outside aggro range but within casting range... but that was when I was level 61 and the mobs were YELLOW cons.  Basicaly, once the mob was in flee-mode, I had to say close enough to see the nametag above his head, otherwise I'd risk self-healing.  This was INDEPENDENT of my HPs.<br /><br />After Ding 62, they became WHITE cons, and I only had to be within casting range to avoid the self heal.  There were a few times I wasn't paying attention and ran out of static-aggro range (or "/say" range) and went "oh shit" when I noticed the mobs HP at 12% or so (self buffed). Then I turned around to run back, but I saw that it was already standing there in flee-mode and wasn't self-healing.<br /><br />We all know that aggro-range is affected by level.  Only in flee-mode, it's the reverse.  <br /><br />Makes sense when ya think about it.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
