                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I've done tons of aggro kiting in PoV and the original poster is correct. Depending on MY hps at the time the crawler or golem I'm kiting will flee at different health percentages.<br /><br />The distance at which they flee and will super regen is not max casting range IMO, but close to it. I just try to stay somewhat near the mob when it gets to 15% (with Virtue) or 9% (self-buffed). When it turns and stops moving you're cool. If it moves toward you, then away from the wall, then toward you again, etc. you are too far and run the risk of it healing.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
